ard Validation**"],"metadata":{"id":"CzE9AQbnnJZS"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["u_pass= input(\"Enter your Passward\")\n","u_pass_p = r\"^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)(?=.*[@$!%*?&])[A-Za-z\\d@$!%*?&]{8,}$\"\n","\n","if re.match(u_pass_p,u_pass):\n","   print(\"########\")\n","else:\n","   print(\"Invalid Passward\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"SDzCkyJmnJB4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783783415548,"user_tz":-360,"elapsed":15714,"user":{"displayName":"Md Nafizur Rahman","userId":"18146873080813533499"}},"outputId":"6b825343-fc49-44c3-c399-631c02e034d0"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Enter your PasswardRu@vet!19\n","########\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["u_pass= input(\"Enter your Passward\")\n","u_pass_p = r\"^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)(?=.*[@$!%*?&])[A-Za-z\\d@$!%*?&]{8,}$\"\n","\n","if re.match(u_pass_p,u_pass):\n","   print(\"########\")\n","else:\n","   print(\"Invalid Passward\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"BP4nt1bLxxv5","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783783454035,"user_tz":-360,"elapsed":9622,"user":{"displayName":"Md Nafizur Rahman","userId":"18146873080813533499"}},"outputId":"4b691e00-7927-4562-e0cb-6768574181d0"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Enter your PasswardRU@VET\n","Invalid Passward\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **User phone number validation ** - **My assign Home work**\n","How this Regex (phone_pattern) Works:\n","^ : Indicates the start of the string.\n","\n","(?:\\+?88)? : This makes the country code optional. It will match +88, 88, or nothing at all.\n","\n","01 : Ensures the actual number starts with 01.\n","\n","[3-9] : Ensures the third digit is a valid operator code in Bangladesh (e.g., 3 for Banglalink, 7 for Grameenphone, etc.).\n","\n","\\d{8} : Ensures there are exactly 8 more numbers after the operator code.\n","\n","$ : Indicates the end of the string (so the user can't type a 15-digit number and still pass)."],"metadata":{"id":"DB0Nz_c7yaMY"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import re\n","\n","# Ask the user for their phone number\n","u_phone = input(\"Enter your phone number: \")\n","\n","# Regex pattern for Bangladeshi phone numbers\n","# It accepts: 01XXXXXXX, 8801XXXXXXXX, or +8801XXXXXXXX\n","phone_pattern = r\"^(?:\\+?88)?01[3-9]\\d{8}$\"\n","\n","# Validate using re.match\n","if re.match(phone_pattern, u_phone):\n","    print(\"Valid Phone Number!\")\n","else:\n","    print(\"Invalid Phone Number. Please check the format.\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"Zskyw8i_ybn5","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783783746899,"user_tz":-360,"elapsed":7880,"user":{"displayName":"Md Nafizur Rahman","userId":"18146873080813533499"}},"outputId":"f4d3659a-5ea9-40b8-fa3f-63955c840c50"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Enter your phone number: 01849288024\n","Valid Phone Number!\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **International_pattern**\n","How this Regex (international_pattern) Works:\n","^ : Starts reading from the very beginning of the string.\n","\n","\\+ : Ensures the very first character is a plus sign (+). We need the backslash \\ because a + normally has a special math meaning in regex.\n","\n","[1-9] : Ensures the first number right after the + is between 1 and 9 (country codes never start with a 0).\n","\n","\\d{6,14} : Ensures there are between 6 and 14 more digits after that. (According to global telecom standards, an international phone number maxes out at 15 total digits).\n","\n","$ : Ensures nothing else comes after the numbers (so no hidden letters or extra long numbers).\n","\n","If you run this, typing +8801711223344 will pass, +12025550177 will pass, but typing 01711223344 will fail because it is missing the mandatory + and country code!"],"metadata":{"id":"gjT2178S0k9N"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import re\n","\n","u_phone = input(\"Enter your international phone number: \")\n","\n","# Regex pattern for generic international format (E.164 standard)\n","# Example valid formats: +8801712345678 (BD), +14155552671 (US), +447911123456 (UK)\n","international_pattern = r\"^\\+[1-9]\\d{6,14}$\"\n","\n","if re.match(international_pattern, u_phone):\n","    print(\"Valid International Phone Number!\")\n","else:\n","    print(\"Invalid format. It must start with '+' followed by the country code and number.\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"uMf1TGD20Q7j","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783784111776,"user_tz":-360,"elapsed":13216,"user":{"displayName":"Md Nafizur Rahman","userId":"18146873080813533499"}},"outputId":"4e8ace36-375c-4a45-e8d2-d0741d1672d2"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Enter your international phone number: +8801316928988\n","Valid International Phone Number!\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# **Python Debugging**"],"metadata":{"id":"70QYpwt-n6k8"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#pylint - analysis tools that gives python scores\n","!pip install pylint\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"collapsed":true,"id":"6bZj_PtWn-zE","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1783780931632,"user_tz":-360,"elapsed":9683,"user":{"displayName":"Md Nafizur Rahman","userId":"18146873080813533499"}},"outputId":"221adc3b-433a-49b0-d38e-21ef9a8157ab"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Collecting pylint\n","  Downloading pylint-4.0.6-py3-none-any.whl.metadata (12 kB)\n","Collecting astroid<=4.1.dev0,>=4.0.2 (from pylint)\n","  Downloading astroid-4.0.4-py3-none-any.whl.metadata (4.4 kB)\n","Requirement already satisfied: dill>=0.3.6 in /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages (from pylint) (0.3.8)\n","Collecting isort!=5.13,<9,>=5